27
00:04:49,122 --> 00:04:51,852
Just one? So what?

28
00:04:53,426 --> 00:05:00,628
On top ofthis gate, you"ll fi nd
at least five or six unclaimed bodies.

29
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:03,761
You"re right.

30
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:08,466
War, earthquake, winds,

31
00:05:09,842 --> 00:05:13,903
fi re, famine, the plague...

32
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:17,243
Year afteryear,
it"s been nothing but disasters.

33
00:05:22,388 --> 00:05:27,087
And bandits descend upon us
every night.

34
00:05:28,728 --> 00:05:36,100
I"ve seen so many men
getting killed like insects,

35
00:05:37,937 --> 00:05:44,137
but even I have never heard
a story as horrible as this.

36
00:05:50,249 --> 00:05:53,810
Yes. So horrible.

37
00:05:57,824 --> 00:06:03,660
This time, I may fi nally lose
my faith in the human soul.

38
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:09,229
It"s worse than bandits,
the plague,

39
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:16,039
famine, fi re, orwar.

40
