51
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:48,330
It was three days ago.

52
00:07:49,068 --> 00:07:52,868
I went into the mountains
to get wood.

53
00:11:34,927 --> 00:11:37,259
Iranas fastas Icould
to tell thepolice.

54
00:11:38,297 --> 00:11:42,597
Then, three days later-- today--
I was calledto testify.

55
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:47,900
Yes. That"s right.

56
00:11:51,911 --> 00:11:57,543
I was the one
who fi rst found the body.

57
00:11:57,817 --> 00:12:01,014
What? Did I see a sword
or something?

58
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,918
No, nothing at all.

59
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:08,956
Just a woman"s hat
caught on a branch,

60
00:12:10,329 --> 00:12:13,821
and the cap ofa samurai
that had been trampled on.

61
00:12:14,533 --> 00:12:18,196
There was a cut-up piece ofrope
near the body,

62
00:12:20,005 --> 00:12:27,207
and further along in the leaves,
a shiny amulet case with red lining.

63
00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:29,007
Yes.

64
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:35,979
That was all I found, yes.

65
00:12:37,623 --> 00:12:39,250
Yes.

66
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:45,761
I met the murdered man
before his death.

67
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:52,666
It was three days ago,
in the afternoon.

68
00:12:54,507 --> 00:12:58,739
On the road from Sekiyama
to Yamashina.

69
00:13:16,762 --> 00:13:23,258
The womanhada veil,
so Icouldn'tseeherface.

70
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:31,205
Theman was armedwith asword,
as wellas abowandarrows.

71
00:13:35,181 --> 00:13:42,178
Little did I expect
that he would meet such a fate.

72
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:51,257
A human life is truly as frail
and feeting as the morning dew.

73
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:57,926
What a shame
that his should end this way.

74
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:00,862
I"m sorry.

75
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:09,047
This man I caught is Tajomaru.

76
00:14:10,249 --> 00:14:15,277
Yes, the notorious bandit
everyone speaks of.

77
00:14:17,823 --> 00:14:22,658
The last time I almost caught him,
he looked the same

78
00:14:22,828 --> 00:14:25,228
and he carried that same sword.

79
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:31,865
It was two days ago at dusk,
by the banks ofthe Katsura...

80
00:14:48,921 --> 00:14:52,755
What"s wrong?

81
00:15:04,003 --> 00:15:07,871
There were 17arrows
with eagle feathers,

82
00:15:07,973 --> 00:15:12,501
aleatherbow, andahorse.

83
00:15:13,412 --> 00:15:17,314
All these belonged
to the dead man, yes.

84
00:15:19,451 --> 00:15:24,787
The irony ofTajomaru being
thrown off his stolen horse,

85
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:27,521
this had to be fateful retribution.

86
00:15:35,901 --> 00:15:40,167
I fell off the horse?
You fool!

87
00:15:44,543 --> 00:15:46,010
On that day...

88
00:15:55,254 --> 00:15:57,848
I was riding that horse
and I was suddenlyvery thirsty.

89
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,418
So around Osaka,
I drank from a spring.

90
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:17,370
There must have been
a dead poisonous snake upstream.

91
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:21,174
After a while, I got
an incredible stomachache.

92
00:16:22,081 --> 00:16:26,575
By the time I came to the river,
I couldn"t hold it any longer.

93
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:31,553
So I got off the horse
and crouched in the field.

94
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:39,096
I fell off?

95
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:42,360
Obviously, a fool can think only
foolish thoughts.

96
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:49,004
I know sooner or later
you"ll have my neck,

97
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:52,168
so I"m not going to hide anything.

98
00:16:55,247 --> 00:16:57,875
It was this Tajomaru
who killed that man.

99
00:17:01,153 --> 00:17:04,714
I saw that couple three days ago.
It was a hot afternoon.

100
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:09,252
Suddenly a cool breeze
rustled the leaves.

101
00:17:10,662 --> 00:17:15,395
Ifit hadn"t been for that wind,
I wouldn"t have killed him.

102
00:19:49,488 --> 00:19:53,720
I caught a glimpse
and then she was gone.

103
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,691
Maybe that"s why.

104
00:19:57,196 --> 00:20:00,461
I thought I saw a goddess.

105
00:20:01,099 --> 00:20:04,330
At that moment I decided to capture her,
even ifI had to kill her man.

106
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:13,037
But ifI could have her
without killing, all the better.

107
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:18,676
My intention then was to take her
without killing the man.

108
00:20:21,019 --> 00:20:24,420
But I couldn"t do it
on that road to Yamashina.

109
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,732
What doyou want?

110
00:20:56,355 --> 00:20:57,413
What doyou want?

111
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:09,792
What is it?

112
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,351
Don"t be suspicious.

113
00:21:35,961 --> 00:21:38,054
See? Isn"t this nice?

114
00:21:41,066 --> 00:21:42,624
Take a good look at it.

115
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:53,537
There are some ruins over there.

116
00:21:54,579 --> 00:22:00,347
When I dug up the mound, I found
a heap ofswords and mirrors.

117
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:05,147
I buried them in a grove behind the mountain
so no one else would fi nd them.

118
00:22:06,958 --> 00:22:10,086
Ifyou"re interested,
I"ll sell them toyou cheap.

119
00:23:45,824 --> 00:23:47,189
It"s over there.

120
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:51,323
Walk ahead ofme.

121
00:24:36,241 --> 00:24:39,108
It"s here. Beyond those pines.

122
00:26:33,625 --> 00:26:37,721
Your husband
has taken sick.

123
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:52,699
Her face turned pale.
She stared at me with frozen eyes,

124
00:26:53,011 --> 00:26:56,640
her expression intense like a child"s.

125
00:26:58,083 --> 00:27:02,577
When I saw that, I envied the man
and I suddenly hated him.

126
00:27:03,455 --> 00:27:07,585
I wanted to show her how pathetic
he looked tied to that pine tree.

127
00:27:08,126 --> 00:27:12,495
These thoughts that weren"t there
before fi lled my head.

128
00:28:47,492 --> 00:28:49,824
Ihadneverseen
such fierceness in a woman.

129
00:31:13,137 --> 00:31:17,506
And so I had succeeded in having her
without killing her husband.

130
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:26,944
I still had no intention
ofkilling him.

131
00:31:28,753 --> 00:31:30,277
But then...

132
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:33,951
Wait!

133
00:31:35,426 --> 00:31:36,984
Stop!

134
00:31:37,962 --> 00:31:42,456
Eitheryou die or my husband dies.

135
00:31:43,268 --> 00:31:45,463
One ofyou must die.

136
00:31:56,214 --> 00:32:01,481
To have my shame known to two men
is worse than dying.

137
00:32:04,822 --> 00:32:13,161
I will go with the survivor.

138
00:35:08,506 --> 00:35:11,441
So I had to kill him,
but I wanted to do it honorably.

139
00:35:12,009 --> 00:35:16,378
He fought verywell.
We crossed swords 23 times.

140
00:35:17,615 --> 00:35:22,279
I remember this
because I"m still impressed.

141
00:35:23,087 --> 00:35:26,545
No one had ever crossed swords
with me more than 20 times.

142
00:35:31,028 --> 00:35:33,656
What? The woman?

143
00:35:35,933 --> 00:35:38,094
I don"t know.

144
00:35:38,603 --> 00:35:44,303
When the man died,
I turned to her. She was gone.

145
00:35:45,910 --> 00:35:50,279
The fighting must have scared her
and she ran away.

146
00:35:51,315 --> 00:35:53,909
I ran out to the mountain road.

147
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:57,054
All I found was her horse
grazing calmly.

148
00:35:58,689 --> 00:36:02,523
I was attracted to her fierce spirit,

149
00:36:02,693 --> 00:36:06,595
but, after all, she wasjust
like otherwomen.

150
00:36:07,231 --> 00:36:09,131
I didn"t even look for her.

151
00:36:12,403 --> 00:36:14,997
What? His sword?

152
00:36:16,941 --> 00:36:19,466
I exchanged it in town for liquor.

153
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:24,012
What? Her dagger?

154
00:36:26,584 --> 00:36:32,853
It had pearl inlay.
Looked veryvaluable.

155
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:38,955
I totally forgot about it.
That was foolish.

156
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:41,698
The biggest mistake I ever made!

157
00:37:04,021 --> 00:37:09,721
Even amongst the bandits,
Tajomaru is famous for being a womanizer.

158
00:37:11,562 --> 00:37:16,727
Why, last fall, a young wife went
to the temple and she and her maid

159
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:22,601
were found dead in the mountains.
That must have been him too.

160
00:37:29,513 --> 00:37:33,950
Who knows what really happened
to that woman who left her horse?

161
00:37:40,157 --> 00:37:43,388
Well, that woman showed up
at the courthouse.

162
00:37:46,831 --> 00:37:52,861
She was hiding in the temple
when the police found her.

163
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:54,662
It"s a lie.

164
00:37:55,506 --> 00:37:59,203
It"s all a lie.
Tajomaru"s story and the woman"s.

165
00:38:00,411 --> 00:38:02,606
It"s human to lie.

166
00:38:06,984 --> 00:38:10,249
Most ofthe time we can"t even
be honest with ourselves.

167
00:38:10,421 --> 00:38:12,184
That may be.

168
00:38:18,162 --> 00:38:26,729
But it"s because men are weak
that they lie, even to themselves.

169
00:38:26,937 --> 00:38:28,871
Not another sermon.

170
00:38:29,874 --> 00:38:34,208
I don"t care ifit"s a lie,
as long as it"s entertaining.

171
00:38:37,381 --> 00:38:39,611
What story did the woman
come up with?

172
00:38:40,885 --> 00:38:45,788
Well, it"s completely different
from Tajomaru"s story.

173
00:38:48,092 --> 00:38:55,521
So different that her face didn"t even
show the fierceness he spoke of.

174
00:39:02,907 --> 00:39:05,899
She was so docile,
she was almost pitiful.

175
00:39:35,005 --> 00:39:37,030
That man in the blue kimono,

176
00:39:40,478 --> 00:39:43,311
after forcing me toyield to him,

177
00:39:44,648 --> 00:39:50,177
proudly announced that
he was the infamous Tajomaru,

178
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:57,725
and laughed mockingly at my husband
who was tied up.

179
00:40:08,806 --> 00:40:16,508
How horrified my husband
must have been.

180
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:23,178
The more he struggled,

181
00:40:25,990 --> 00:40:33,226
the tighter the ropes dug in.

182
00:40:36,333 --> 00:40:42,932
I ran to his side. Or rather, I tried to.

183
00:42:31,282 --> 00:42:37,243
Even now, when I think ofhis eyes,

184
00:42:38,756 --> 00:42:42,658
my blood turns cold in myveins.

185
00:42:46,497 --> 00:42:50,866
What I saw in them was neither anger,

186
00:42:52,336 --> 00:42:53,803
nor sorrow,

187
00:42:55,372 --> 00:43:04,178
but a cold light, a look ofloathing.

188
00:43:11,822 --> 00:43:13,483
Don"t.

189
00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:16,452
Don"t look at me like that.

190
00:43:21,565 --> 00:43:22,896
It"s too cruel.

191
00:43:24,635 --> 00:43:26,728
Beat me,

192
00:43:27,705 --> 00:43:34,474
kill me, but don"t look at me like that.
Please, stop.

193
00:44:59,096 --> 00:45:01,257
Now kill me.

194
00:45:02,332 --> 00:45:04,732
Kill me at once.

195
00:45:38,869 --> 00:45:40,359
Stop.

196
00:45:41,872 --> 00:45:43,931
Don"t.

197
00:45:49,012 --> 00:45:50,604
Please don"t.

198
00:46:34,558 --> 00:46:40,394
I must have fainted after that.

199
00:46:49,973 --> 00:46:52,533
When I came to
and looked around...

200
00:47:01,151 --> 00:47:03,676
Imagine my shock.

201
00:47:20,470 --> 00:47:28,741
I saw my dagger
in my dead husband"s chest.

202
00:47:43,393 --> 00:47:46,829
I was in shock

203
00:47:49,900 --> 00:47:52,801
and I don"t remember
how I left the woods.

204
00:47:59,042 --> 00:48:01,272
But when I came to,

205
00:48:05,115 --> 00:48:07,083
I was standing by the pond,

206
00:48:08,785 --> 00:48:10,548
at the foot ofthe hill.

207
00:48:17,961 --> 00:48:20,088
I threw myselfinto the pond.

208
00:48:22,299 --> 00:48:26,258
I tried many different things.

209
00:48:28,105 --> 00:48:32,439
But I failed to kill myself.

210
00:48:44,855 --> 00:48:56,289
What should a poor,
helpless woman like me do?

211
00:49:31,969 --> 00:49:35,268
I see. The more I hear,
the more confused I get.

212
00:49:38,208 --> 00:49:41,405
But women use their tears
to fool everyone.

213
00:49:42,079 --> 00:49:43,876
They even fool themselves.

214
00:49:45,449 --> 00:49:48,714
Soyou have to beware
ofthe woman"s story.

215
00:49:50,988 --> 00:49:53,320
When you hear
the dead man"s story--

216
00:49:54,224 --> 00:49:59,287
He"s dead.
How can he tell his story?

217
00:50:00,230 --> 00:50:02,061
He spoke through a medium.

218
00:50:04,067 --> 00:50:07,833
Lies. His storywas also lies.

219
00:50:10,640 --> 00:50:14,838
But dead men don"t lie.

220
00:50:15,846 --> 00:50:17,541
Why is that?

221
00:50:19,549 --> 00:50:22,484
I refuse to believe
that man would be so sinful.

222
00:50:24,154 --> 00:50:25,587
Suityourself.

223
00:50:26,656 --> 00:50:28,590
But is there anyone who"s
really good?

224
00:50:29,459 --> 00:50:32,360
Maybe goodness isjust make-believe.

225
00:50:32,462 --> 00:50:34,726
What a frightening--

226
00:50:35,465 --> 00:50:38,025
Manjust wants to forget
the bad stuff

227
00:50:38,935 --> 00:50:41,130
and believe in the made-up
good stuff.

228
00:50:41,505 --> 00:50:43,871
It"s easier that way.
- Ridiculous.

229
00:50:47,677 --> 00:50:49,269
Nevermind.

230
00:50:49,379 --> 00:50:52,109
Let"s hear the dead man"s story.

231
00:51:39,729 --> 00:51:43,062
I am in darkness now.

232
00:51:43,166 --> 00:51:47,603
I am suffering in the dark.

233
00:51:48,472 --> 00:51:53,307
Cursed be those who cast me
into this dark hell.

234
00:52:31,414 --> 00:52:38,411
After the bandit attacked mywife,
he tried to console her.

235
00:52:40,023 --> 00:52:45,290
Shesaton theleaves,
staring down atherknees.

236
00:52:46,696 --> 00:52:49,460
Thebandit was cunning.

237
00:52:50,467 --> 00:52:52,833
Nowthather virtue was stained,

238
00:52:53,003 --> 00:52:55,471
she couldnolongerbe
with herhusband.

239
00:52:55,639 --> 00:52:58,938
Leave thehusband
andwhynotmarryhim instead?

240
00:52:59,609 --> 00:53:03,272
He saidhe onlyattackedher
outofhis love forher.

241
00:53:05,048 --> 00:53:09,610
Whensheheard that,
my wife raisedherfaceas ifin a trance.

242
00:53:16,293 --> 00:53:21,890
She had never looked so beautiful.

243
00:53:28,638 --> 00:53:35,339
Andwhat was mybeautiful wife's
response to thebandit

244
00:53:36,713 --> 00:53:38,704
in frontofherhelpless husband?

245
00:53:42,219 --> 00:53:43,914
Wherever.

246
00:53:46,690 --> 00:53:49,181
Take me whereveryou want.

247
00:53:51,161 --> 00:53:53,322
That"s what she said.

248
00:53:56,633 --> 00:53:59,193
But that wasn"t her only sin

249
00:54:00,070 --> 00:54:04,200
or I wouldn"t be suffering
